{"key":"processedPost-11121844","value":{"id":11121844,"first":11120934,"last":11122200,"when":1253847761,"utime":"09/25/09 06:02 AM","content":"You don't use fans on flowhoods, you use blowers.&nbsp; A fan will cavitate rather than blow through something like a flow hood.&nbsp; A blower for the smallest 12\" X 24\" flowhood filter will need to be at least 1/5 HP and have a squirrel cage blower attached.&nbsp; Make sure it's rated at the flow you require at +/- 1\" W.G.<br />RR","title":"Re: Flow hood build help"}}